  <Fragment slot="lead">
    <p class="lead">
      If you searched for the <strong>best AeroPress alternative</strong>, you probably want one of two things:
      a different flavor style, or a workflow that fits your mornings better. Good news — this choice is easier than it
      looks.
    </p>
    <p>
      Think of AeroPress like a quick, tidy weeknight dinner. French Press is more like a slow Sunday meal: richer,
      heavier, and a little messier. Neither is wrong. You just need the one that matches how you actually brew when you
      are half-awake and running late.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="quick-verdict">
    <p>
      <strong>Quick verdict:</strong> For most single-cup drinkers, <strong>AeroPress</strong> is the better daily tool.
      It is fast, forgiving, and almost no-mess. But if your favorite coffee feels thick and cozy — more like hot
      chocolate texture than tea-like clarity — <strong>French Press</strong> is usually the better pick and the more
      common AeroPress alternative.
    </p>
    <p>
      Want a clean middle path? Pour-over gives cleaner flavor than French Press and more ritual than AeroPress. Want
      bold, punchy cups with stovetop simplicity? Moka pot can be a strong alternative too. We will break all of that
      down below in plain English.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

